                  </hi>. I was on London-bridge with the prosecutor, who said he had lost his handkerchief—he turned round and collared the prisoner who dropped it at his side—the prosecutor took it up, then took the prisoner to Fenchurch-street, and gave him to a policeman with the handkerchief</p>
